<subSubSection id="7DFF2EFC763AFFF1FADFF335E2DFFDE8" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="510" pageId="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="355A7D77763AFFF1FADFF335E2DFFDE8" blockId="21.[1395,2601,3240,3357]" lastBlockId="22.[806,1390,286,712]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="510" pageId="21">
Taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F4763AFFF2F992F335E090F300" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1866" box="[1592,1688,3275,3308]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Stenella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="21" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Stenella</taxonomicName>
is currently in dispute. The genus is likely polyphyletic and probably will be revised in the near future. According to molecular studies, 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F4763AFFF2F6D4F30CEC02F2FF" baseAuthorityName="G. Cuvier" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[2430,2570,3314,3347]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Stenella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="21" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="frontalis">S. frontalis</taxonomicName>
is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FBD8FEE0E325FED3" baseAuthorityName="Meyen" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1138,1325,286,319]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Stenella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="coeruleoalba">S. coeruleoalba</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FC82FEB7E5A2FE8A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1850" box="[808,938,329,358]" class="Mammalia" family="Delphinidae" genus="Delphinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clymene">S. clymene</taxonomicName>
, followed by 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FBC3FEB7E2E3FE8A" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1129,1259,329,358]" class="Mammalia" family="Delphinidae" genus="Delphinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Delphinus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FA93FEB7E5D3FE62" baseAuthorityName="Ehrenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1833" class="Mammalia" family="Delphinidae" genus="Tursiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aduncus">Tursiops aduncus</taxonomicName>
. These species appear to be more closely related to each other than any of them are to 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FBEAFE45E2D6FE30" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[1088,1246,443,476]" class="Mammalia" family="Delphinidae" genus="Tursiops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cetacea" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="truncatus">1. truncatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FB5BFE45E558FDE8" pageId="22" pageNumber="510">S. attenuata</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="F2E506F47639FFF1FC2BFE1DE224FDE8" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[897,1068,483,516]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Mycosphaerellaceae" genus="Stenella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Capnodiales" pageId="22" pageNumber="510" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="longirostris">S. longirostris</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="619A2DFF763AFFF2FFD0F28EEF23F265" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6611005" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6611005" box="[122,2347,3440,3465]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6611005/files/figure.png" pageId="21" startId="21.[122,152,3440,3465]" targetBox="[12,2768,12,3655]" targetPageId="20">
